From: knsol <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH] fix: write a01.txt to /SD:/ root instead of /SD:/audio/

After patches 0036+0037, fs_open still returns -ENOENT for
/SD:/audio/a01.txt even with valid FS_O_WRITE|FS_O_CREATE flags.
mount_sd_card reports the audio directory was created (or already
existed via FR_EXIST), but the path stays unresolvable.

Side-stepping the issue: drop the subdirectory entirely and write
to /SD:/a01.txt at the root. info.txt at /SD:/ root works fine via
the same fs_open flag pattern (proved at boot), so root-level
writes are known good on this Zephyr/FATFS combo.

This is a temporary debug fix to confirm whether subdirectory access
is the root cause or whether something else is broken downstream.
---
diff --git a/omi/firmware/devkit/src/sdcard.c b/omi/firmware/devkit/src/sdcard.c
--- a/omi/firmware/devkit/src/sdcard.c
+++ b/omi/firmware/devkit/src/sdcard.c
@@ -235,7 +235,13 @@ int write_to_file(uint8_t *data, uint32_t length)
      * returns -EINVAL on every call, which strongly suggests
      * write_buffer is corrupted/empty by the time write_to_file is
      * invoked. Hardcoded path removes the static-buffer dependency. */
-    const char *target_path = "/SD:/audio/a01.txt";
+    /* Patch 0038: try root-level path. fs_open returned -ENOENT for
+     * /SD:/audio/a01.txt with FS_O_WRITE | FS_O_CREATE even though
+     * mount_sd_card claims /SD:/audio exists (mkdir returned EEXIST).
+     * Suspect the directory isn't properly accessible; skip the
+     * subdirectory entirely. wr_chunk's rotation logic uses absolute
+     * paths so dropping the subdir doesn't break it. */
+    const char *target_path = "/SD:/a01.txt";
     /* Patch 0037: drop FS_O_APPEND. With FS_O_WRITE | FS_O_APPEND |
      * FS_O_CREATE Zephyr/FATFS returns -ENOENT here even though the
      * parent dir exists. Same flags minus APPEND work fine for
